    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Description\n\nThere are some servers that allow adding custom language support, or could be language agnostic despite having support list.\n\nIn legacy interface, to set such servers to launch for any filetype was just `filetypes = { '*' }`, however the new interface uses lack of this parameter for that.\n\nEven explicit \n```lua\nvim.lsp.config(name, conf)\nvim.lsp.config[name].filetypes = nil\n```\nseems to get overridden by value provided in lspconfig.\n\nIt would be helpful if old `'*'` was still honored.\n\n---\n\nRelated to #3838 ",
