        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Since it seems we won't get anything sensible (at least not anytime soon), what's left is to rely on such workarounds:\n```lua\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"BufReadPre\", {\n    once = true,\n    callback = function()\n      for s,_ in pairs(vim.lsp.config[\"_\" .. \"configs\"]) do\n        if vim.tbl_contains(vim.lsp.config[s].filetypes or {\"*\"}, \"*\") then\n          vim.lsp.config[s].filetypes = nil\n        end\n      end\n    end\n  })\n```\n\nNote: setting `filetypes` to `nil` must happen **after** call to `vim.lsp.enable()`\n\n<sub>Hopefully, nobody will break access to configs via `vim.lsp.config._configs`</sub>",
